      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PEACEFUL RULER (3) made an impression, comfortably winning a Bunbury Maiden on debut. Resumed owning a Lark Hill trial win and missed 1L at over 1300m at Belmont. Overcame a tough run and with the extra fitness he can take this out. MEDIA MOGUL (2) raced forward and improved sharply easily winning his Maiden over 1200m at a short quote. The money came again at Belmont following where he led beaten a nose. Peaks today and is a decent chance to bounce. ROMANCE CALLING (7) has needed her two runs this preparation. She posted a competitive number winning a Northam Maiden at her only third-up outing. Has 3kg weight relief, maps well and the tongue tie is applied for the first time. THE SCHOLAR (1) will use the inside gate to advantage and finds easier. In the mix.",
